This is the first “real” hazard.

The source calls find_water_level, may write gShadowAboveWaterOrLava = TRUE, and has a documented missing return statement that “incidentally” returns waterLevel unless AVOID_UB is enabled. 

IR sketch:

def get_water_level_below_shadow_ir (s : Ptr Shadow) : IR :=
  let waterLevel ← call find_water_level [load s.parentX, load s.parentZ]
  ifIR (waterLevel < FLOOR_LOWER_LIMIT_SHADOW)
    (return 0.0)
    (ifIR ((load s.parentY >= waterLevel) &&
           (load s.floorHeight <= waterLevel))
      (seq
        (store8 (global gShadowAboveWaterOrLava) TRUE)
        (return waterLevel))
      (compilerArtifactReturn "missing return; IDO returns waterLevel incidentally"))
Effect summary:

{
  "function": "get_water_level_below_shadow",
  "reads": [
    "s->parentX",
    "s->parentY",
    "s->parentZ",
    "s->floorHeight",
    "collision/water environment via find_water_level"
  ],
  "writes": [
    "gShadowAboveWaterOrLava"
  ],
  "calls": [
    "find_water_level"
  ],
