What I would not do
I would not try to write a full C-to-Lean transpiler for all of SM64 first. That is too broad.

I would not trust a JSON summary unless it is generated from AST/IR and reproducible.

I would not use Frama-C/CBMC/SeaHorn as the final story without a proof-assistant artifact, because the “world’s first proof” claim benefits from a small, inspectable, machine-checked theorem over a generated model.

I would not model all RDRAM unless the proof needs it. Use byte-addressed memory for load/init/effect preservation; use symbolic abstractions for gameplay reachability.

